I"ô<ol>
  <li>Preheat the oven to 180C.</li>
  <li>Remove the cheese from its packaging. Cut a circle of baking paper 2cm larger in diameter than the cheese and place the wheel of camembert on it.</li>
  <li>Using a sharp knife, score the top of the Camembert in a crisscross pattern. Bake for about 10-15 minutes or until the cheese is melting and the rind has started to caramelise.</li>
  <li>Carefully remove cheese from the oven.</li>
  <li>Serve with toasted sourdough, fruit and nuts.</li>
</ol>
